replyContent: We're sorry to hear you are not satisfied with the app. By design, users cannot delete locations, but via the website (fallingfruit.org), it is possible to flag locations for removal. content: The latest version of the app added the ability to filter results by food-type, bringing it up to speed with the website. Much better for dumpster diving now! (though the filter search is case sensitive, which is odd.) replyContent: Thanks for your feedback, Dylan. The latest version (0.2) now allows you to filter by edible type. "Tree inventories" are exhaustive tree databases, typically produced by cities and universities, added to Falling Fruit; these can be toggled off to make it easier to find user-added locations. Hope that helps. Happy foraging!

What web features would like to see in the app? We're a small volunteer-run nonprofit and the (free) website costs us thousands of dollars per year. Mobile app sales help cover our operating costs.

replyContent: Adding, editing, and reviewing locations has been supported since the first version. To add a new location, press the placemark icon with the '+' in the bottom right of the screen, fine tune the location's position, confirm by pressing the checkmark, fill out the form, then hit save. Hope that helps. Happy foraging!
